100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 25, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, focusing on international peace efforts amid growing tensions in Europe. In the United States, the ongoing Scopes Trial continued to capture national attention as debates over evolution and education unfolded in Tennessee. Meanwhile, in India, Mahatma Gandhi was arrested, drawing widespread condemnation and sparking protests against British colonial rule.
